[gd_scene load_steps=21 format=3 uid="uid://b0embergrave_s1room02_wide_chunk"]

; S1 tile-quality rework + lined-hall colonnade (ticket 86ca44p4j; Uma spec
; team/uma-ux/s1-tile-rework.md §2.3/§3/§4). Supersedes the reuse-only PR #407
; pass (Sponsor REJECTED on feel 2026-06-03: "not a lined hall, objects out of
; place, does not block user, tile design not nice").
;
; THREE fixes stacked here:
;   1. FLOOR/WALL render as the FULL 128-px crafted AI image tiled (4-tile
;      period) via the S1CloisterChunk 4×4 atlas-window painter — kills the
;      single-32px-tile wallpaper repeat. (Painter change, not this scene.)
;   2. COLONNADE: 8 pillars in 2 mirrored rows (north y≈64 / south y≈208),
;      4/row at x≈200/420/640/860, vertically aligned, framing a CLEAR aisle
;      (y≈112–176). 3 lit braziers north wall (x≈310/530/750, BETWEEN pillars),
;      1 cold brazier south (x≈530). 2 banners north (x≈420/640, over the
;      central bays). Settle-decoration (rubble/parchment/moss) at column-feet
;      + corners.
;   3. COLLISION: pillars + braziers + large rubble are SOLID StaticBody2D on
;      layer 1 (world) — blocks player (mask=1) AND grunt (mask=3). Footprint
;      box at the prop BASE, smaller than the sprite. Small rubble / parchment
;      / moss / banner = NO collision. Aisle stays clear, gaps ≥2 tiles, every
;      grunt-spawn reaches the player around the colonnade (Grunt uses direct
;      steering + move_and_slide, NOT a NavigationAgent — small base-footprints
;      keep the colonnade permeable so a chaser deflects around, never wedges).
;
; Geometry (ground-truth from resources/level_chunks/s1_room02_wide.tres):
;   30×8 tiles @ 32px = 960×256. Interior walkable x∈[32,928] y∈[32,224].
;   Entry port (0,4)→y144, exit (29,4)→y144 ⇒ aisle = y≈144.
;   Grunt spawns: (10,3)=(320,96) (15,5)=(480,160) (21,3)=(672,96) (25,5)=(800,160).
;
; The four perimeter Wall* StaticBody2D nodes are UNCHANGED (BB-3 invariant);
; the colonnade collision is NEW SolidProps StaticBody2D children, decoupled
; from the visual Sprite2D under Props.

